    <label>bitter orange</label>
    <description>A fresh, sour orange. All oranges are globose and contain pulp that consists of oblong vesicles that are filled with a sugary, refreshing juice, segregated into multiple "compartments." This type of orange is called a bitter orange (taxonomy &lt;i>Citrus aurantium&lt;/i>), which is created by crossing Mandarin oranges with pomelos. \n Along with citrons and pomelos, the original Mandarin orange (taxonomy &lt;i>Citrus reticulata&lt;/i>) is one of the core components of every other citrus crop that exists.</description>
