  <ThingDef ParentName="RoughPlantBase">
    <defName>ST_Bean</defName>
    <label>glitter bean</label>
    <description>Beans are the seeds of the legume plant (taxonomic family &lt;i>Fabaceae&lt;/i>, also called &lt;i>Leguminosae&lt;/i>), a type of flowering plant native to Old Earth and naturally spread throughout every one of its continents except Antarctica (before its development). Beans require warmer temperatures to grow and as such grew naturally in a range from tropical to temperate Biomes. nn \n The glitter bean, so named because of its association with extremely powerful Glitter World technology, is a highly nutritious staple of many diets on the Rim as much as it is on Core Worlds. (Its usage on Glitter Worlds is mainly limited to the eccentric Glitter citizens enlightening Bulborbs into Bean Men.) \n \n When combined with the highly advanced Sapient Bean Matrix and a dedicated Bean Pit, it can be used to give human-level sapience to the normally primitive Bulborbs that naturally frolic across many planets in the galaxy.</description>
	<descriptionHyperlinks>
		<RecipeDef>MakeSapientBeanMatrix</RecipeDef>
